{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Inductor Energy Storage",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Inductor Energy Storage",
    "description": "USB → tact → 470Ω → T split. East: 470Ω + red LED (your indicator — stays on while you hold the button). West: slide switch → inductor → ground (charge the coil only when the switch connects that branch). Straights at row 8 tie the coil node to the LED node. With the switch ON, hold the tact several seconds, then release — a brief pulse on the east LED as stored field energy dumps (much shorter than lesson 20’s capacitor fade). Flip the switch OFF and repeat: little or no afterglow. Compare lesson 20 (long cap discharge) and lesson 41 (series kickback flash). Slide switch at 180°; east LED at 90° (anode north)."
  },
